<DATELINE>LOS ANGELES (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The <ORGANIZATION> Associated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> erroneously reported Friday that jurors found divorce attorney <PERSON> Marvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Mitchelson </PERSON> innocent in a civil lawsuit filed by a former client who had accused him of legal malpractice in her 1984 divorce case. The verdict was actually a two-part ruling. Jurors found that <PERSON> Mitchelson </PERSON> had failed to exercise the care and skill ordinarily used by an attorney in such cases. But the jury refused to assess any damages against <PERSON> Mitchelson </PERSON>, ruling that his failure had not injured his former client. In a separate finding, jurors denied a counter-suit filed by <PERSON> Mitchelson </PERSON> seeking unpaid legal fees for handling the divorce case.
