<DATELINE>TALLAHASSEE, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Three state child-welfare workers were suspended and a fourth has quit following the death of a 2-year-old boy whose parents allegedly dunked him repeatedly in a toilet for soiling his diapers. The workers ignored guidelines in returning <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON> <PERSON> McGee </PERSON> to his mother and stepfather, ignoring warnings that they were abusing the boy, the <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Health </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Rehabilitative </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> said Friday. <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON> died of a brain hemorrhage July 28, shortly after the HRS workers returned the boy to his parents from foster care. <PERSON> Sheryl </PERSON> <PERSON> McGee </PERSON> <PERSON> Coe </PERSON>, 20, and <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Edward </PERSON> <PERSON> Coe </PERSON>, 22, both of <LOCATION> Lakeland </LOCATION>, were held without bond Friday facing first-degree murder charges in the case. HRS Secretary <PERSON> Gregory </PERSON> <PERSON> Coler </PERSON> said he was upset that the staffers recommended the child be returned to the Coes despite the abuse reports and their failure to fulfill an agreement to attend drug-abuse counseling. `` We're not talking about facts that were n't known or somebody who did n't show up somewhere or that the information was n't there,'' <PERSON> Coler </PERSON> said Thursday, the day of <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON>'s funeral `` We're talking about people not following procedure. <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON> was taken from the Coes' custody in March 1988 after HRS officials said the Coes had been negligent. He was returned to them in late May despite the warnings of <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON>'s foster parents, the <LOCATION> Kirklands </LOCATION>. The foster parents said they repeatedly told HRS workers that they feared <PERSON> Bradley </PERSON> would be in danger if returned to the Coes. Three ch