ht forward and a tiny steering wheel. An 11-foot by 6 -LCB- - foot rectangular solar panel sits flat atop the body, with a small bubble in the middle for the driver `` It's actually comfortable,'' said the 6-foot 4-inch <PERSON> Kerry </PERSON>, looking decidedly uncomfortable as he sat in the car. The vehicle is powered by a small electric motor that can get the car up to 90 mph. <PERSON> Worden </PERSON>'s prototype clearly has limitations _ he could not get the vehicle to get over a curb to get to the site of the news conference _ but it has responsive turning and fast pick up. The designer raced around the Capitol parking lot at speeds that ordinarily would bring a warning from security guards. <PERSON> Worden </PERSON>, wearing a white racing jumpsuit and flashing a thumbs up sign, said the team had few troubles other than a couple of flats in <LOCATION> Louisiana </LOCATION>. But the traditional gas-powered truck that brought the solar car from <LOCATION> Massachusetts </LOCATION> to <LOCATION> California </LOCATION> broke down.
