ON> States </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Pakistan </LOCATION> of U.N.-mediated accords that were supposed to stop <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> arms supplies to the mujahedeen and Soviet arms supplies to the Afghan army. He welcomed <PERSON> Perez </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Cuellar </PERSON>'s call Friday for a peaceful settlement of the 10-year-old civil war but said it was `` not enough.'' The Afghan government hopes <PERSON> Perez </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Cuellar </PERSON> will play `` a more active and more serious role than he has played so far,'' <PERSON> Amani </PERSON> said, noting he has been authorized to visit <LOCATION> Kabul </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Islamabad </LOCATION> to try to end the war.
