<TEXT>
 A previously unknown group claimed in a statement published today that a man killed in a <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> hotel explosion was preparing an attack on British author <PERSON> Salman </PERSON> <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON>. <PERSON> Rushdie </PERSON> has been in hiding in <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION> since Feb. 14, when the late Iranian leader <PERSON> Ayatollah </PERSON> <PERSON> Ruhollah </PERSON> <PERSON> Khomeini </PERSON> said his novel `` The Satanic Verses'' blasphemed Islam and called on Moslems to kill the author. <LOCATION> Scotland </LOCATION> Yard said a man was killed Thursday as he worked with a handmade explosive charge inside a <LOCATION> London </LOCATION> hotel near <LOCATION> Paddington </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Station </LOCATION>. The statement from a group calling itself the <ORGANIZATION> Organization </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Islam </ORGANIZATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Mujahedeen </ORGANIZATION> did not identify the man, which it said was the group's `` first martyr.''
